$1.87</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font><br></font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">NEW YORK</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">, January&#160;30, 2025 &#8211; Marsh McLennan (NYSE&#58; MMC), the world&#8217;s leading professional services firm in the areas of risk, strategy and people, today reported financial results for the fourth quarter and year ended December&#160;31, 2024.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">John Doyle, President and CEO, said&#58; &#34;Our fourth quarter results capped a terrific year for Marsh McLennan. We delivered on our strategic objectives, generated excellent financial performance, and had the largest year of acquisitions in our history. For the full year, we generated 7% underlying revenue growth, 10% adjusted EPS growth and 80 basis points of adjusted margin expansion, marking our 17th consecutive year of reported margin expansion.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">&#34;We are well positioned for another strong year in 2025, reflecting our unique capabilities and the enduring value we bring to clients.&#34;</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Consolidated Results</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Consolidated revenue in the fourth quarter of 2024 was $6.1 billion, an increase of 9% compared with the fourth quarter of 2023, or 7% on an underlying basis. Operating income was $1.1 billion. Adjusted operating income, which excludes noteworthy items as presented in the attached supplemental schedules, rose 9% to $1.3 billion. Net income attributable to the Company was $788 million. Earnings per share increased 5% to $1.59. Adjusted earnings per share increased 11% to $1.87 and included a benefit of 5 cents per share from favorable discrete tax items, as well as a headwind of 2 cents per share from foreign exchange. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:63pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center;text-indent:36pt"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:99.553%"><tr><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:47.778%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:31.635%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td><td style="width:1.0%"></td><td style="width:17.287%"></td><td style="width:0.1%"></td></tr><tr style="height:15pt"><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"><div><img alt="image.jpg" src="image.jpg" style="height:12px;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:288px"></div></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td><td colspan="3" style="padding:0 1pt"></td></tr></table><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">1</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">For the full year 2024, revenue was $24.5 billion, an increase of 8% compared with 2023, or 7% on an underlying basis. Operating income was $5.8 billion, and adjusted operating income rose 11% to $6.2 billion. Net income attributable to the Company was $4.1 billion. Earnings per share increased 9% to $8.18. Adjusted earnings per share increased 10% to $8.80. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Risk &#38; Insurance Services</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Risk &#38; Insurance Services revenue was $3.6 billion in the fourth quarter of 2024, an increase of 11%, or 8% on an underlying basis. Operating income was $770 million. Adjusted operating income increased 13% to $893 million. For the year 2024, revenue was $15.4 billion, an increase of 9% compared with 2023, or 8% on an underlying basis. Operating income was $4.4 billion. Adjusted operating income rose 13% to $4.6 billion.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Marsh's revenue in the fourth quarter of 2024 was $3.3 billion, an increase of 15%, or 8% on an underlying basis. In U.S.&#47;Canada, underlying revenue rose 8%. International operations produced underlying revenue growth of 9%, including 13% in Latin America, 9% in EMEA, and 6% in Asia Pacific. For the year 2024, Marsh&#8217;s revenue growth was 10% compared to a year ago, or 7% on an underlying basis.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Guy Carpenter's fourth quarter revenue was $201 million, a decrease of 20%, or an increase of 7% on an underlying basis. For the year 2024, Guy Carpenter&#8217;s revenue grew 5% compared to a year ago, or 8% on an underlying basis.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Consulting</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Consulting revenue was $2.4 billion in the fourth quarter of 2024, an increase of 6% on both a GAAP and underlying basis. Operating income was $466 million. Adjusted operating income increased 1% to $484 million. For the year 2024, revenue was $9.1 billion, an increase of 5% compared with 2023, or 6% on an underlying basis. Operating income was $1.8 billion. Adjusted operating income increased 6% to $1.8 billion. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Mercer&#8217;s revenue was $1.5 billion in the fourth quarter of 2024, an increase of 3%, or 5% on an underlying basis. Wealth revenue increased 4% on an underlying basis, Health revenue increased 5% on an underlying basis, and Career revenue increased 7% on an underlying basis.</font><font style="color:#ff0000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">For the year 2024, Mercer&#8217;s revenue increased 3%, or 5% on an underlying basis.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Oliver Wyman&#8217;s revenue was $954 million in the fourth quarter of 2024, an increase of 11%, or 7% on an underlying basis. For the year 2024, Oliver Wyman&#8217;s revenue was $3.4 billion, an increase of 9%, or 6% on an underlying basis. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Other Items</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company repurchased 4.3 million shares for $900 million in 2024. </font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">On November 15, 2024, the Company completed the acquisition of McGriff Insurance Services, LLC (&#34;McGriff&#34;), a leading provider of insurance broking and risk management services in the United States, for $7.75 billion in cash consideration. As part of funding for the transaction, the Company issued $7.25 billion of senior notes on November 8, 2024.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font><br></font></div><div style="height:63pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">2</font></div></div></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%;text-decoration:underline">Conference Call</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:11pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">A conference call to discuss fourth quarter 2024 results will be held today at 8&#58;30 a.m. Eastern time. The live audio webcast may be accessed at marshmclennan.com. A replay of the webcast will be available approximately two hours after the event. The webcast is listen-only. Those interested in participating in the question-and-answer session may register here to receive the dial-in numbers and unique PIN to access the call.</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">About Marsh McLennan</font></div><div style="margin-bottom:10pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Marsh McLennan</font><font style="color:#0000ff;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(NYSE&#58; MMC) is a global leader in risk, strategy and people, advising clients in 130 countries across four businesses&#58;  Marsh, Guy Carpenter, Mercer and Oliver Wyman. With annual revenue of over $24 billion and more than 90,000 colleagues, Marsh McLennan helps build the confidence to thrive through the power of perspective. For more information, visit marshmclennan.com, follow us on LinkedIn and X.</font></div><div style="height:63pt;position:relative;width:100%"><div style="bottom:0;position:absolute;width:100%"><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">3</font></div></div></div><div id="i2851069928564677ab82e8fa08a4e448_10"></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div style="margin-bottom:9pt;margin-top:5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">INFORMATION CONCERNING FORWARD-LOOKING STATEMENTS</font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">This press release contains &#34;forward-looking statements,&#34; as defined in the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Three Months Ended December 31</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(Millions) (Unaudited)</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The Company advises clients in 130 countries. As a result, foreign exchange rate movements may impact period over period comparisons of revenue. Similarly, certain other items such as acquisitions and dispositions, including transfers among businesses, may impact period over period comparisons of revenue. Non-GAAP underlying revenue measures the change in revenue from one period to the next by isolating these impacts.</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><table The Comp</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:7.5pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">any has included reconciliations of these non-GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable financial measure calculated in accordance with GAAP in the following tables.</font></div></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:7.5pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">The Company believes these non-GAAP financial measures provide useful supplemental information that enables investors to better compare the Company&#8217;s performance across periods. Management also uses these measures internally to assess the operating performance of its businesses and to decide how to allocate resources. However, investors should not consider these non-GAAP measures in isolation from, or as a substitute for, the financial information that the Company reports in accordance with GAAP. The Company's non-GAAP measures include adjustments that reflect how management views its businesses, and may differ from similarly titled non-GAAP measures presented by other companies.</font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:bottom"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:7.5pt;font-weight:700;line-height:100%">Adjusted Operating Income (Loss) and Adjusted Operating Margin</font></td></tr><tr><td colspan="3" style="padding:2px 1pt;text-align:left;vertical-align:top"><div><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:7.5pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:100%">Adjusted operating income (loss)</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:7.5pt;font-weight:400;line-height:100%"> is calculated by excluding the impact of certain noteworthy items from the Company's GAAP operating income (loss). McLennan Companies, Inc.</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%"> Reconciliation of Non-GAAP Measures</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Three and Twelve Months Ended December 31 </font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(In millions, except per share data)</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> (Unaudited)</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted income, net of tax </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">is calculated as the Company's GAAP income from continuing operations, adjusted to reflect the after tax impact of the operating income adjustments in the preceding tables and the additional items listed below. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Adjusted EPS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> is calculated by dividing the Company&#8217;s </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">adjusted income, net of tax</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">, by the average number of shares outstanding-diluted for the relevant period. The following tables reconcile </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">adjusted income, net of tax</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> to GAAP income from continuing operations and </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">adjusted EPS</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> to GAAP EPS for the three and twelve months ended December 31, 2024 and 2023</font><font style="background-color:#ffffff;color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:9pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">. </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">13</font></div></div></div><div id="i2851069928564677ab82e8fa08a4e448_597"></div><hr style="page-break-after:always"><div style="min-height:54pt;width:100%"><div><font><br></font></div></div><div><font><br></font></div><div id="i2851069928564677ab82e8fa08a4e448_43"></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Marsh &#38; McLennan Companies, Inc.</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Reconciliation of Non-GAAP Measures</font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:700;line-height:120%">Three Months Ended December 31  </font></div><div style="text-align:center"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:10pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">(Millions) (Unaudited)</font></div><div style="margin-top:12pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">Non-GAAP revenue</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> isolates the impact of foreign exchange rate movements and certain transaction-related items from the current period GAAP revenue. The </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">non-GAAP revenue</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> measure is presented on a constant currency basis, excluding the impact of foreign currency fluctuations. The Company isolates the impact of foreign exchange rate movements period over period, by translating the current period foreign currency GAAP revenue into U.S. Dollars based on the difference in the current and corresponding prior period exchange rates. Similarly, certain other items such as acquisitions and dispositions, including transfers among businesses, may impact period over period comparisons of revenue and are consistently excluded from current and prior period GAAP revenues for comparability purposes. Percentage changes, referred to as </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">non-GAAP underlying revenue</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">, are calculated by dividing the period over period change in </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">non-GAAP revenue</font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%"> by the prior period </font><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-style:italic;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">non-GAAP revenue.  </font></div><div style="margin-top:5pt"><font style="color:#000000;font-family:'Arial',sans-serif;font-size:8pt;font-weight:400;line-height:120%">The following table provides the reconciliation of GAAP revenue to non-GAAP revenue&#58;</font></div><div style="margin-top:8pt"><table style="border-collapse:collapse;display:inline-table;margin-bottom:5pt;vertical-align:text-bottom;width:100.000%"><tr><td enables investors to better compare the Company&#8217;s performance across periods. Management also uses these measures internally to assess the operating performance of its businesses and to decide how to allocate resources. However, investors should not consider these non-GAAP measures in isolation from, or as a substitute for, the financial information that the Company reports in accordance with GAAP. // Edgar(tm) Renderer was created by staff of the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission.  Data and content created by government employees within the scope of their employment are not subject to domestic copyright protection. 17 U.S.C. 105.
var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
